\title{Topological Constraints Command}
\description{
An \link[R6:R6Class]{R6} class that holds one or more topological
constraints and renders the TNT \code{force} command to apply them during
tree searches in \pkg{nitro}.

Each constraint is either a \link{MonophylyConstraint}, which constrains a
named set of taxa to be monophyletic or non-monophyletic, or a
\link{BackboneConstraint}, which constrains the search to recover a topology
compatible with a reference tree. Multiple constraints of either type
can be combined in a single \code{TopologicalConstraintsCommand}.

Constraints are activated during a search by a companion
\link{ConstrainCommand} object, which is enqueued automatically by
\code{\link[=set_constraint]{set_constraint()}}.
}
\details{
\subsection{Command output}{

\verb{$render()} produces one or more \code{force} statements of the form:
\itemize{
\item Positive monophyly: \verb{force + [ TaxonA TaxonB TaxonC ];}
\item Negative monophyly: \verb{force - [ TaxonA TaxonB ];}
\item With floating OTUs: \verb{force + [ TaxonA TaxonB (TaxonC TaxonD) ];}
\item Positive backbone: \verb{force / &0;}
\item Negative backbone: \verb{force : &0;}
}
}

\subsection{Queue integration}{

Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds this command to a \link{CommandQueue} at priority
\code{401}. A \link{ConstrainCommand} enabling constraint enforcement is added
separately at priority \code{411} by \code{\link[=set_constraint]{set_constraint()}}.
}

\subsection{Dependencies}{
\itemize{
\item \code{"matrix"} (required) — a \link{ReadDataCommand} object. Used to validate
that all taxon names in the constraints are present in the matrix.
\item \code{"reference tree"} (optional) — a \link{ReadTreesCommand} object. Required
when any constraint is a \link{BackboneConstraint}.
}
}
}
